O. B. Clarence https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/O._B._Clarence 0 Oliver Burchett Clarence (25 March 1870, Hampstead, London – 2 October 1955, Hove, Sussex) was an English actor.Following his education at Dover College and University College Hospital, he made his stage debut in 1890. His experience included Shakespearean repertory with Frank Benson and Ben Greet. He performed in over eighty shows in London and also toured the provinces and appeared abroad too.
